2016-08-30 15:08 UTC+0300 Alexander Kresin <alex@belacy.ru>
  * include/guilib.ch
  * source/gtk/hedit.prg
  * source/winapi/hedit.prg
    * ON PAINT clause deleted from @ ... EDITBOX command as unused

2016-08-30 11:35 UTC+0300 Alexander Kresin <alex@belacy.ru>
  * source/winapi/hbrowse.prg
  + source/winapi/hbrwflt.prg
    * All code, related to filtering, moved from HBrowse to a new subclass HBrwFlt
  * include/guilib.ch
    * New command added @ ... BROWSE ... FILTER for HBrwFlt
      So, if you use those WHILE, FIRST, LAST, FOR clauses of BROWSE ... DATABASE
      command, use BROWSE ... FILTER instead.
  * makefile*
    * makefiles updated for a new source file hbrwflt.prg

2016-08-29 15:41 UTC+0300 Alexander Kresin <alex@belacy.ru>
  * source/winapi/hwindow.prg
  * source/winapi/hedit.prg
    * Color in Focus handling has been changed.
      Now there are 3 levels:
      1) a global one, the same as before - it works for all GET's in all windows
      2) a window level: you can define colors in focus, using;
         hwg_SetColorinFocus( oWindow, tColor, bColor ) function - the same as bafore,
         but oWindow (oDlg) is passed instead of lDef;
      3) a GET level: you may set colors in focus for any GET, using a new HEdit variable:
         bColorBlock, which is called while WM_SETFOCUS, get as a parameter the HEdit
         object and should call :Setcolor() method to set colors.
      Thanks to SergKis for the idea.

2016-08-29 13:54 UTC+0300 Alexander Kresin <alex@belacy.ru>
  * include/guilib.ch
    * BACKCOLOR added as preferrable alternative for COLOR clause in INIT WINDOW,
      INIT DIALOG commands.
    * added #xtranslate hwg_ParentGetDialog => hwg_getParentForm
  * source/gtk/gtkmain.prg
    * hwg_getParentForm( oCtrl ) added.
  * source/gtk/hedit.prg
  * source/winapi/hedit.prg
    * hwg_getParentForm() is used now instead of hwg_ParentGetDialog(),
      hwg_ParentGetDialog() is deleted.
    ! Some fixes for 'tab' key.

2016-08-24 13:27 UTC+0300 Alexander Kresin <alex@belacy.ru>
  * source/gtk/htree.prg
    ! Small fix

2016-08-24 11:24 UTC+0300 Alexander Kresin <alex@belacy.ru>
  * source/gtk/hpanel.prg
  * source/winapi/hpanel.prg
    * :aItems variable and :DrawItems() method has been added to make it more easy
      to draw items on a panel control:
         Aadd( oPanel:aItems, { cId, {|hDC,aCoors|SomeDrawFunc(hDC,aCoors,...)} )
  * source/gtk/draw.c
  * source/gtk/hcombo.prg
    * The drawable areas in gtk ( such as PANEL with SS_OWNERDRAW style ) doesn't
      allow buttons (including check- and radiobuttons), clicable part of a combobox
      to display. Now this is fixed for comboboxes by redrawing this part on a
      drawable panel.

