2013-06-13 17:37 UTC+0200 Przemyslaw Czerpak (druzus/at/priv.onet.pl)
  * hwgui/include/guilib.ch
    * added workaround for some ancient Harbour and xHarbour compilers
      which may not define __PLATFORM__UNIX
    * define __GTK__ for *nix builds

  * hwgui/gtk/hwinprn.prg
  * hwgui/gtk/hprinter.prg
  * hwgui/gtk/hfrmtmpl.prg
  * hwgui/source/procmisc/scrdebug.prg
  * hwgui/source/procmisc/hfrmtmpl.prg
  * hwgui/utils/debugger/hwgdebug.prg
    * use __GTK__ macro instead of __LINUX__

  * hwgui/source/procmisc/procscri.prg
  * hwgui/source/debug/dbgconnect.prg
    * use __PLATFORM__UNIX macro supported by Harbour and xHarbour
      instead of manually defined __LINUX__ macro

  * hwgui/source/hwinprn.prg
    * use __GTK__ macro instead of __PLATFORM__Linux__
      Please verify me. such macro never existed in Harbour
      and xHarbour (only __PLATFORM__Linux) so maybe code
      covered by it should be removed?

  * hwgui/samples/winprn/winprn.prg
    * use __PLATFORM__UNIX macro supported by Harbour and xHarbuor
      instead of __PLATFORM__Linux__
      Please verify me. such macro never existed in Harbour
      and xHarbour (only __PLATFORM__Linux) so maybe code
      covered by it should be removed?

